# Case-class body methods dispatch on the native lane

Regression for `v2-imported-receiver-methods-not-linked` (gap 2): a `:`-indented
case-class body with 2+ methods must all dispatch — earlier only the first did (the
rest leaked as top-level defs → `Stub`). Built-in names on other receivers (List.size)
must NOT be hijacked.

```scalascript
case class ByteSlice(data: List[Int]):
  def get(i: Int): Int = data(i)
  def size(): Int = data.length

val base = ByteSlice(List(10, 20, 30, 40, 50))
println(base.get(4))
println(base.size())
println(List(1, 2, 3).size)
```
